<p>The Mangyongdae Childrenâ€™s Palace was full of children super talented in both performing and visual arts. This picture breaks my heart because our minders were showing off this place as a point of pride, but everything in this room seemed strangely familiarâ€¦ and then I realised: These were the same kinds of artwork that we were being pushed to buy in all the souvenir/book stores they took us to. At that point it went from â€˜Wow, these kids are talented!â€™ to â€˜Am I witnessing child slave labour?â€™</p>

<p>Iâ€™m still not sure if Iâ€™m just being cynical, or if my gut reaction is founded.</p>

